cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.HC 

The paper presents an approach to generate novel computer game levels using machine learning techniques. The use of analogical reasoning and probabilistic models suggests that the paper belongs to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The focus on level design and gameplay videos suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Graphics (cs.GR). The use of computer vision techniques to analyze gameplay videos suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the evaluation of the system's ability to explain levels blended by human expert designers suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
